&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOT&lt;/strong&gt; another boring job ad where we bullet point all of&amp;nbsp; the responsibilities, obvious traits, and qualifications. Who wants to read all of that? We have a different vibe here at IntelliChoice. We just celebrated&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;17 years of care&lt;/strong&gt;, and we did so as a small, family owned company.&lt;strong&gt; Nothing corporate about us! &lt;/strong&gt;We’re not just filling shifts—we’re building meaningful relationships in our schools and communities across North Carolina.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re not “just staff.” You’re the kind of human we cheer for, invest in, and brag about. We celebrate wins, support each other, and make sure you love BOTH your job&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;and&lt;/em&gt; get balance back in your life.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt; color: rgb(186, 55, 42);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Highlight Reel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE NEED&lt;/strong&gt;: Speech Language Pathologist (SLP)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing school-based speech therapy to an awesome group of students. A good mix of articulation impairments to students who are using AAC devices for functional communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Survive telling a 2nd grader “let’s try that sound again” 14 times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manageable case loads with a ton of support, we let no one drown!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with teachers, families, and support staff who &lt;em&gt;actually respond to calls and emails&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Writing IEPs that make sense (and don’t steal your soul or make you ugly cry)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Making real progress with kids—and celebrating it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And the obvious Masters Degree and Active License to practice in NC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Perks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great WEEKLY pay and flexible schedule-who wants to be stuck in an office all day?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with fun, curious students in a great small-town school district&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive school team and a brigade of a clinical support team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make a real difference (and hear some hilarious kid stories along the way)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oh and the BEST Boss Ever!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 18pt; color: rgb(186, 55, 42);&quot;&gt;Let’s connect and see if this is your next fit!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 18pt; color: rgb(186, 55, 42);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8pt; color: rgb(186, 55, 42);&quot;&gt;#RDU&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍎 School-Based Certified Occupational Therapy Assistant&amp;nbsp; – K-12 |&amp;nbsp; Coolest Kids In Town &amp;amp;&amp;nbsp; Best Boss Ever!💙&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking for a job where your biggest challenge might be opening a glue stick or avoiding snacking with the cool kids? We’re hiring a School-Based Occupational Therapist to support amazing K-12 students while working with a team that truly values you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;✨ Perks of the Job: &lt;strong&gt;Well first is our company, and your boss, are a whole new vibe you need in your life!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;📚 School schedule = holidays, weekends &amp;amp; summers off--um heck yeah!&lt;br&gt;🧃 Snacks may randomly appear in meetings-oh and coffee, lots of coffee&lt;br&gt;💙 Highly Supportive team environment where we are your biggest fan&lt;br&gt;🎉 Meaningful work that changes kids’ lives daily and is fun&lt;br&gt;☀️ Work-life balance actually exists here at IntelliChoice!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll help students build confidence and independence through therapy services that make a lasting impact — all while surviving glitter, group projects, and school spirit week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications/Desired Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Licensed Occupational Therapist Assistant by the state of North Carolina&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or equivalent and an associate degree in occupational therapy from an accredited OTA program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in school-based or pediatric settings preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(186, 55, 42);&quot;&gt;Hit Apply and Let&#39;s Connect!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot; data-start=&quot;704&quot; data-end=&quot;759&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;710&quot; data-end=&quot;757&quot;&gt;🌟&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speech-Language Pathology Assistant– Amazing Schools, Cool Students, and a Highly Supportive Team! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;710&quot; data-end=&quot;757&quot;&gt;🌟&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join a truly supportive and welcoming school community with the BEST students and a collaborative team that truly values the team, where you’re appreciated, and never working alone. We are seeking a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;SLPA &lt;/strong&gt;for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;107&quot; data-end=&quot;142&quot;&gt; K-12 assignments&lt;/strong&gt;— because a group of energetic elementary students are waiting for someone who knows their &lt;strong data-start=&quot;234&quot; data-end=&quot;275&quot;&gt;/r/ sounds from their recess stories.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;277&quot; data-end=&quot;468&quot;&gt;If you can:&lt;br data-start=&quot;288&quot; data-end=&quot;291&quot;&gt;✔ Turn speech therapy into a game&lt;br data-start=&quot;324&quot; data-end=&quot;327&quot;&gt;✔ Survive telling a 2nd grader “let’s try that sound again” 14 times&lt;br data-start=&quot;395&quot; data-end=&quot;398&quot;&gt;✔ Handle knock-knock jokes and random dinosaur facts during sessions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;470&quot; data-end=&quot;513&quot;&gt;…then you are &lt;strong data-start=&quot;489&quot; data-end=&quot;513&quot;&gt;exactly who we need!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎁 The Perks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great weekly pay and flex schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with fun, curious students&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive school team and a brigade of a clinical support team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make a real difference (and hear some hilarious kid stories along the way)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships within the school system for future opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oh and the BEST BOSS EVER!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✨ What Your Days Look Like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the supervising Speech-Language Pathologist in providing speech, language, and communication services to students with IEPs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct speech and language screenings under the direction and supervision of the SLP-teamwork makes the dreamwork&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manageable case loads with a ton of support, we let no one drown!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with teachers, families, and support staff who &lt;em&gt;actually respond to calls and emails&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IEPs and activities that make sense (and don’t steal your soul or make you ugly cry)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Making real progress with kids—and celebrating it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✨ &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State Requirements - Education, Licensure, and Certification:&amp;nbsp;One of the following: (a) associate&#39;s degree in speech-language pathology assisting from an accredited institution; or (b) bachelor&#39;s degree in communication sciences and disorders from an accredited institution, plus required coursework in speech-language pathology assisting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NC state SLPA license or authorization&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completion of an accredited SLPA certification program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior pediatric or school experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-s

&lt;h3&gt;Join our team as a Night Owl Nurse where the vibes are calmer, the traffic is better, caffeine and late-night snacks are never judged. ☕&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;✨ Flexible schedules&lt;br&gt;✨ Supportive team (yes, really like any hour you can call someone and get a human)&lt;br&gt;✨ Weekly pay&lt;br&gt;✨ 1:1 patient care&amp;nbsp; because that is how it should be!&lt;br&gt;✨ Low-drama, high-impact nursing with a family owned anti-corporate company where you are a person not a badge #.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(186, 55, 42);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;💙&lt;/span&gt;🌟Where Work is Family 🌟&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;💙 &amp;nbsp;We just celebrated 17 years of care, and we did so as a small, family owned company. Nothing corporate about us!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;At IntelliChoice Home Care, you’re not just “staff” — you’re family. We celebrate wins together, support each other through challenges, and make sure you love the work you do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;This isn’t just a “clock in, clock out” job. It’s showing up for someone who truly needs you and working for a company that truly values you. We’re hiring Rockstar Nurses(LPN or RN) for cases across North Carolina—where you care for one client at a time &lt;strong&gt;(yes, ONE!)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
